quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  9,124,"And whenever there comes down a Sûrah (chapter from the Qur’ân), some of them (hypocrites) say: "
  9,125,"But as for those in whose hearts is a disease (of doubt, disbelief and hypocrisy), it will add suspicion and doubt to their suspicion, disbelief and doubt; and they die while they are disbelievers."
  9,126,"See they not that they are put in trial once or twice every year (with different kinds of calamities, disease, famine)? Yet, they turn not in repentance, nor do they learn a lesson (from it)."
  10,82,""
  10,83,"But none believed in Mûsâ (Moses) except the offspring of his people, because of the fear of Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) and his chiefs, lest they should persecute them; and verily, Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) was an arrogant tyrant on the earth, he was indeed one of the Musrifûn (polytheists, sinners and transgressors, those who give up the truth and follow the evil, and commit all kinds of great sins)."
  10,84,"And Mûsâ (Moses) said: "
  11,49,"This is of the news of the Unseen which We reveal unto you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم); neither you nor your people knew it before this. So be patient. Surely, the (good) end is for Al-Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2)"
  11,50,"And to ‘Âd (people We sent) their brother Hûd. He said, "
  11,51,""
  12,10,"One from among them said: "
  12,11,"They said: "
